The paper proposes a new algorithm for approximate maximum a posteriori (MAP) inference on factor graphs, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses experiments on synthetic and real-world problems, indicating a focus on practical applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of factors for imposing first-order logic constraints, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL).
